title: The Saga of the Candy Scroll

Message.message: This is a game made in two days for #candyjam. Enjoy!
Act 1: Candy World
Mr. Candy is stuck in the magical land of Candy World.
Help him escape by clearing all of the candies!
Walk up to a candy and press X to add it to your Candy Scroll.
Level 1
"Wow, this Candy Scroll is cool! It can crus--I mean CLEAR three candies in a row!" said Mr. Candy.
Mr. Candy wonders what original game mechanics he will encounter next.
Level 2
Mr. Candy wonders why the candies are being dropped into different columns of the Candy Scroll, and decides to investigate further.
Should he fail in his endeavors, he need only press R to restart the level.
Level 3
It appears that approaching candies from different directions determines their placement on the Candy Scroll.
Enlightened, Mr. Candy continues his quest to clear ALL of the candies.  Not crush, obviously.  There is only one King when it comes to crushing candies, and Mr. Candy is clearly not him.
Level 4
Level 5
Level 6
Mr. Candy continues through Candy World and notices something odd.
"Is that a green candy? I love those!"
Level 7
Level 8
Mr. Candy advances further and discovers yet another color of candies.  He must be getting close to the exit!
Level 9
Mr. Candy notices something in the distance, and is ecstatic.
"Hey, look! It's the Super Candy Diamond! If I can clear it, I will certainly be able to escape Candy World!"
Level 10
Mr. Candy escapes from Candy World! He is delighted to return to civilization...but this delight is fleeting.
He is assaulted by evil ninjas and dragged into an interrogation room!
"Mr. Candy, we regret to inform you that your name is trademarked.  By choosing to be known as Mr. Candy, you create brand confusion and must change your name immediately."
Mr. Candy replies, "This is complete nonsense!" He tries to escape, but is not fast enough to escape the ninjas!
He loses consciousness...
Act 2: The Prison
Mr. Candy finds himself locked in a prison. It looks a lot like Candy World, but there are ninjas blocking his escape!
He suspects that he must defeat all of the ninjas before he can escape, but he doesn't know how.
Sadly, he begins clearing candies...
Level 11
Incredible! The Candy Scroll can defeat ninjas!
Eager to test the Candy Scroll's limits, Mr. Candy proceeds through the prison.
Level 12
"Interesting," Mr. Candy says. "I can only kill ninjas with my Candy Scroll if I am vertically or horizontally aligned with them."
Level 13
Level 14
"Wow, the Candy Scroll's ninja-destroying powers even reach through walls! I'll be out of here in no time!"
Level 15
As Mr. Candy makes his way through the prison, he encounters some blue ninjas. Might they bear some connection to the blue candies?
Level 16
Mr. Candy notes that blue ninjas can only be defeated by blue candies, and prepares the Candy Scroll for more battles.
Level 17
Level 18
Level 19
Level 20
Mr. Candy has successfully defeated the ninjas and escaped the prison!
However, his work is not yet finished. He must find those who tried to trademark his name and destroy them!
With his honor and life at stake, he journeys to his enemy's lair...
Act 3: The Palace
Mr. Candy arrives at the palace where his nemesis lives. Inside the palace, he spots some elite green and purple ninjas.
Sensing the battles ahead, the Candy Scroll powers up!  It can now hold even more candy!
Level 21
Level 22
Level 23
Mr. Candy notices an increase in ninjas in the next room. Surely they must be guarding something!
Level 24
After defeating the ninjas, Mr. Candy stumbles upon one of the most magnificent rooms he has ever seen...the Candy Vault!
If he can clear all of this candy, he might be able to defeat the ninjas once and for all!
Level 25
Mr. Candy basks in the glory of his achievement: he has cleared all of the candy!
But suddenly, the palace trembles...
"YOU! YOU CRUSH MY CANDY!" a voice booms.
Startled, Mr. Candy is speechless and looks around for the voice's source...but finds nothing.
"YOU CRUSH KING CRUSHER'S CANDY! NOW KING CRUSHER CRUSH YOU!"
"EAT NINJA!"
Mr. Candy is ambushed! He must defeat King Crusher to escape!
Level 26
"WHAT? YOU DARE DESTROY MY CANDY CROWN?"
"NINJAS! DEFEND ME WHILE I CONSTRUCT A NEW CROWN!"
Level 27
"YOU DEFEAT MY NINJAS...BUT TOO LATE!"
"CANDY CROWN MARK TWO...ACTIVATE!"
Level 28
"MY CANDY BARRIER IS BROKEN? IMPOSSIBLE!"
"NINJAS, DEFEND ME!"
"...NINJAS? YOU THERE?"
"NEVER MIND THEN...I'LL JUST FILL YOUR CANDY SCROLL SO YOU CAN'T DO ANYTHING! BWAHAHA!"
Level 29
"NO...STRENGTH...FLAGGING... ACTIVATE TOTAL CANDY TRANSFORMATION!"
This is it! Take down King Crusher once and for all, and Mr. Candy can take back his name!
Level 30
Mr. Candy has defeated King Crusher and has taken back his name! Future generations of Candies can live in peace, all thanks to the valiant efforts of Mr. Candy...and you, you wonderful person.
Here ends the saga of Mr. Candy and the Candy Scroll.
Thanks for playing!
